2. Double free (CWE-415)

a. Summary of CWE:
This happens when memory is freed more than once, which can cause crashes or security problems.

b. Example C code:

int *ptr = malloc(sizeof(int));
free(ptr);
free(ptr);

c. Remediation (fixed code):

free(ptr);
ptr = NULL;

Explanation:
Setting the pointer to NULL prevents it from being freed again.

d. Mitigation and detection:
Track memory use carefully and use tools to detect memory errors.
